In July 2011, project Kotlin was unveiled by jetBrains, a new programming language for JVM, which had been under
development for a year.
=> In February 2012, jetBrains open sourced the project under the Apache 2 license
=> The name "Kotlin" comes from an island near St.Petersburg just like how Java was named after an Island
=> Kotlin v1.0 was released on February 2016.
    + This is considered to be the first officially stable release
=> Kotlin v1.2 was released on 28 November 2017
    + Sharing code between JVM and Javascript platforms feature was newly added to this release.
=> Kotlin v1.3 was released on 29 October 2018
    + bringing coroutines for asynchronous programming.
=> On 7 May 2019, Google announced that the Kotlin programming language is now its preferred language for
Android app developers.